nd Foote was a sea captain at eighteen, self-taught, fluent in French, Spanish, and Italian, and described as one of the best-educated men of his time. He captained ships until 1826, then moved to Cincinnati where he served as director and unpaid secretary of the water company, director of the Louisville Canal, and rebuilt his fortune after losing it in the financial panic of 1837. During his Cincinnati years his home was the center of the Semi-Colon Club — a literary salon whose members included Salmon P.","number":1,"category":"character"},{"number":2,"category":"character","header":"His salon drew a young Harriet Beecher","body":"At his Cincinnati Semi-Colon Club, the literary salon he hosted, his niece Harriet Beecher — later Stowe — was among the company. The polyglot sea captain lost his fortune in the Panic of 1837 and rebuilt it twice over in canals and insurance."}],"cross_connections":[{"type":"family_orbit","related_id":"X02034","display_label":"was her uncle, host of the salon she frequented","link_text":"Harriet Beecher Stowe"}],"bio":{"display_name":"Samuel Edmund Foote","first_name":"Samuel","last_name":"Foote","middle_name":"Edmund","married_names":[],"bio_blurb":"Sea captain and Cincinnati civic leader"},"residence":{},"baptism":{},"research_tags":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"quotes":[],"military_service":[],"career":[{"role":"Sea captain","notes":"1805-1826"},{"role":"Secretary","organization":"Ohio Life Insurance & Trust Co."},{"role":"Host","organization":"Semi-Colon Club, Cincinnati"}],"slug":"samuel-foote-1787"},"HD0403":{"id":"HD0403","has_descendants_documented":true,"classification":{"include_in_path_calculation":true,"generation_from_thomas":8,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":true,"descent_from_john_talcott":false,"is_thomas_descendant":true,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"birth":{"year":1806,"month":11,"day":16,"city":"Guilford","state":"Co